l towards the front of your chair.";i:29;s:140:"Place your feet shoulder-width apart on the resistance band and face your toes slightly outwards and keep your knees in line with your toes.";i:30;s:201:"Exercise 4 Chair Marching First check your posture Lift alternate legs so that your feet lift about 2 inches from the floor and swing your arms forwards and back at a speed that is comfortable for you.";i:31;s:43:"Imagine you marching along at a brisk pace.";i:32;s:33:"Continue for about 20 30 seconds.";i:33;s:52:"7 Chair-based strength exercises resistance bands 1.";i:34;s:37:"Wrist squeeze twist and pull Purpose.";i:35;s:71:"This will strengthen muscles in the forearms and improve grip strength.";i:36;s:98:"Roll or fold the resistance band into a tube and hold it vertically at stomach or chest height by.";i:37;s:128:"In this video we go through a completely seated strength workout with resistance bands and dumbbells and we work the whole body.";i:38;s:46:"Make sure you do the warm-up before beginning.";i:39;s:22:"PARTIAL SIT TO STANDS.";i:40;s:22:"KNEE EXTENSIONS - RBs.";i:41;s:47:"24 Finding Balance Resistance Band Exercises 9.";i:42;s:72:"Shoulder External Rotation band pull apart Set up and starting position.";i:43;s:154:"Sit up straight in a chair with feet flat on the floor Hold band firmly shoulder width apart in both hands elbows bent at your side with thumbs facing up.";i:44;s:73:"Can you imagine just by sitting in a chair you can do a lot of exercises.";i:45;s:54:"This chair can help you pull up squad and many others.";i:46;s:197:"Take it easy because this is designed to be used when the gym exercises at home this gym chair has a strong material and can also be stored without consuming a lot of space by folding it after use.";i:47;s:27:"Ball Exercises for Seniors.";i:48;s:59:"Best Stability Ball Exercises Medicine Ball Bosu Ball More.";i:49;s:107:"Im going to show you an exercise routine containing just four simple chair based exercises for the elderly.";i: